{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":717,"text":"I'd like to take you on the epic quest\nof the Rosetta spacecraft."},{"time":5514,"text":"To escort and land the probe on a comet,"},{"time":9540,"text":"this has been my passion\nfor the past two years."},{"time":13450,"text":"In order to do that,"},{"time":14545,"text":"I need to explain to you something\nabout the origin of the solar system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":18015,"text":"When we go back\nfour and a half billion years,"},{"time":20238,"text":"there was a cloud of gas and dust."},{"time":21957,"text":"In the center of this cloud,\nour sun formed and ignited."},{"time":26484,"text":"Along with that, what we now know\nas planets, comets and asteroids formed."},{"time":32195,"text":"What then happened, according to theory,"},{"time":35608,"text":"is that when the Earth had cooled down\na bit after its formation,"},{"time":39625,"text":"comets massively impacted the Earth\nand delivered water to Earth."},{"time":45082,"text":"They probably also delivered\ncomplex organic material to Earth,"},{"time":49516,"text":"and that may have bootstrapped\nthe emergence of life."},{"time":52906,"text":"You can compare this to having\nto solve a 250-piece puzzle"},{"time":56366,"text":"and not a 2,000-piece puzzle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":59570,"text":"Afterwards, the big planets\nlike Jupiter and Saturn,"},{"time":63053,"text":"they were not in their place\nwhere they are now,"},{"time":65631,"text":"and they interacted gravitationally,"},{"time":68278,"text":"and they swept the whole interior\nof the solar system clean,"},{"time":71830,"text":"and what we now know as comets"},{"time":73432,"text":"ended up in something\ncalled the Kuiper Belt,"},{"time":75545,"text":"which is a belt of objects\nbeyond the orbit of Neptune."},{"time":79213,"text":"And sometimes these objects\nrun into each other,"},{"time":82906,"text":"and they gravitationally deflect,"},{"time":85971,"text":"and then the gravity of Jupiter\npulls them back into the solar system."},{"time":90428,"text":"And they then become the comets\nas we see them in the sky."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94120,"text":"The important thing here to note\nis that in the meantime,"},{"time":97394,"text":"the four and a half billion years,"},{"time":99693,"text":"these comets have been sitting\non the outside of the solar system,"},{"time":102875,"text":"and haven't changed --"},{"time":104290,"text":"deep, frozen versions of our solar system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107193,"text":"In the sky, they look like this."},{"time":109282,"text":"We know them for their tails."},{"time":111233,"text":"There are actually two tails."},{"time":112904,"text":"One is a dust tail,\nwhich is blown away by the solar wind."},{"time":116759,"text":"The other one is an ion tail,\nwhich is charged particles,"},{"time":120404,"text":"and they follow the magnetic field\nin the solar system."},{"time":123143,"text":"There's the coma,"},{"time":124292,"text":"and then there is the nucleus,\nwhich here is too small to see,"},{"time":127199,"text":"and you have to remember\nthat in the case of Rosetta,"},{"time":129689,"text":"the spacecraft is in that center pixel."},{"time":131866,"text":"We are only 20, 30, 40 kilometers\naway from the comet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":135976,"text":"So what's important to remember?"},{"time":138297,"text":"Comets contain the original material\nfrom which our solar system was formed,"},{"time":143166,"text":"so they're ideal to study the components"},{"time":145526,"text":"that were present at the time \nwhen Earth, and life, started."},{"time":149791,"text":"Comets are also suspected"},{"time":151673,"text":"of having brought the elements\nwhich may have bootstrapped life."},{"time":155944,"text":"In 1983, ESA set up\nits long-term Horizon 2000 program,"},{"time":160309,"text":"which contained one cornerstone,\nwhich would be a mission to a comet."},{"time":164233,"text":"In parallel, a small mission to a comet,\nwhat you see here, Giotto, was launched,"},{"time":169123,"text":"and in 1986, flew by the comet of Halley\nwith an armada of other spacecraft."},{"time":175329,"text":"From the results of that mission,\nit became immediately clear"},{"time":178900,"text":"that comets were ideal bodies to study\nto understand our solar system."},{"time":184087,"text":"And thus, the Rosetta mission\nwas approved in 1993,"},{"time":188599,"text":"and originally it was supposed\nto be launched in 2003,"},{"time":192234,"text":"but a problem arose\nwith an Ariane rocket."},{"time":194858,"text":"However, our P.R. department,\nin its enthusiasm,"},{"time":197923,"text":"had already made\n1,000 Delft Blue plates"},{"time":200145,"text":"with the name of the wrong comets."},{"time":202535,"text":"So I've never had to buy any china since.\nThat's the positive part."},{"time":206102,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":207821,"text":"Once the whole problem was solved,"},{"time":209701,"text":"we left Earth in 2004"},{"time":212882,"text":"to the newly selected comet,\nChuryumov-Gerasimenko."},{"time":215970,"text":"This comet had to be specially selected"},{"time":218826,"text":"because A, you have to\nbe able to get to it,"},{"time":221480,"text":"and B, it shouldn't have been\nin the solar system too long."},{"time":224261,"text":"This particular comet has been \nin the solar system since 1959."},{"time":228208,"text":"That's the first time\nwhen it was deflected by Jupiter,"},{"time":231523,"text":"and it got close enough\nto the sun to start changing."},{"time":234500,"text":"So it's a very fresh comet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":236611,"text":"Rosetta made a few historic firsts."},{"time":239502,"text":"It's the first satellite to orbit a comet,"},{"time":242018,"text":"and to escort it throughout\nits whole tour through the solar system --"},{"time":245640,"text":"closest approach to the sun,\nas we will see in August,"},{"time":248938,"text":"and then away again to the exterior."},{"time":251259,"text":"It's the first ever landing on a comet."},{"time":253860,"text":"We actually orbit the comet\nusing something which is not"},{"time":257552,"text":"normally done with spacecraft."},{"time":259001,"text":"Normally, you look at the sky and you know\nwhere you point and where you are."},{"time":262636,"text":"In this case, that's not enough."},{"time":264772,"text":"We navigated by looking\nat landmarks on the comet."},{"time":268070,"text":"We recognized features --\nboulders, craters --"},{"time":270545,"text":"and that's how we know where we are\nrespective to the comet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":274562,"text":"And, of course, it's the first satellite\nto go beyond the orbit of Jupiter"},{"time":279091,"text":"on solar cells."},{"time":280292,"text":"Now, this sounds more heroic\nthan it actually is,"},{"time":282619,"text":"because the technology\nto use radio isotope thermal generators"},{"time":287715,"text":"wasn't available in Europe at that time,\nso there was no choice."},{"time":291013,"text":"But these solar arrays are big."},{"time":292590,"text":"This is one wing, and these are not\nspecially selected small people."},{"time":295865,"text":"They're just like you and me."},{"time":297699,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":300090,"text":"We have two of these wings,\n65 square meters."},{"time":304291,"text":"Now later on, of course,\nwhen we got to the comet,"},{"time":307310,"text":"you find out that 65 square meters of sail"},{"time":310839,"text":"close to a body which is outgassing\nis not always a very handy choice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":316481,"text":"Now, how did we get to the comet?"},{"time":318525,"text":"Because we had to go there\nfor the Rosetta scientific objectives"},{"time":322193,"text":"very far away -- four times the distance\nof the Earth to the sun --"},{"time":326001,"text":"and also at a much higher velocity\nthan we could achieve with fuel,"},{"time":330111,"text":"because we'd have to take six times as\nmuch fuel as the whole spacecraft weighed."},{"time":334430,"text":"So what do you do?"},{"time":335840,"text":"You use gravitational flybys, slingshots,"},{"time":339323,"text":"where you pass by a planet\nat very low altitude,"},{"time":342690,"text":"a few thousand kilometers,"},{"time":344455,"text":"and then you get the velocity\nof that planet around the sun for free."},{"time":349168,"text":"We did that a few times."},{"time":351211,"text":"We did Earth, we did Mars,\nwe did twice Earth again,"},{"time":353690,"text":"and we also flew by two asteroids,\nLutetia and Steins."},{"time":358318,"text":"Then in 2011, we got so far from the sun\nthat if the spacecraft got into trouble,"},{"time":362983,"text":"we couldn't actually\nsave the spacecraft anymore,"},{"time":366792,"text":"so we went into hibernation."},{"time":368765,"text":"Everything was switched off\nexcept for one clock."},{"time":372103,"text":"Here you see in white the trajectory,\nand the way this works."},{"time":375614,"text":"You see that from\nthe circle where we started,"},{"time":378057,"text":"the white line, actually you get\nmore and more and more elliptical,"},{"time":381873,"text":"and then finally we approached the comet"},{"time":384822,"text":"in May 2014, and we had to start\ndoing the rendezvous maneuvers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":389187,"text":"On the way there, we flew by Earth and we\ntook a few pictures to test our cameras."},{"time":393784,"text":"This is the moon rising over Earth,"},{"time":395962,"text":"and this is what we now call a selfie,"},{"time":397917,"text":"which at that time, by the way,\nthat word didn't exist. (Laughter)"},{"time":401609,"text":"It's at Mars. It was taken\nby the CIVA camera."},{"time":404580,"text":"That's one of the cameras on the lander,"},{"time":406762,"text":"and it just looks under the solar arrays,"},{"time":409177,"text":"and you see the planet Mars\nand the solar array in the distance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413450,"text":"Now, when we got out\nof hibernation in January 2014,"},{"time":419118,"text":"we started arriving at a distance"},{"time":420903,"text":"of two million kilometers\nfrom the comet in May."},{"time":423736,"text":"However, the velocity\nthe spacecraft had was much too fast."},{"time":427845,"text":"We were going 2,800 kilometers an hour\nfaster than the comet, so we had to brake."},{"time":433906,"text":"We had to do eight maneuvers,"},{"time":435763,"text":"and you see here,\nsome of them were really big."},{"time":438340,"text":"We had to brake the first one\nby a few hundred kilometers per hour,"},{"time":444364,"text":"and actually, the duration of that\nwas seven hours,"},{"time":448674,"text":"and it used 218 kilos of fuel,"},{"time":451622,"text":"and those were seven nerve-wracking \nhours, because in 2007,"},{"time":455572,"text":"there was a leak in the system\nof the propulsion of Rosetta,"},{"time":458762,"text":"and we had to close off a branch,"},{"time":460909,"text":"so the system was actually\noperating at a pressure"},{"time":463487,"text":"which it was never designed\nor qualified for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":467795,"text":"Then we got in the vicinity of the comet,\nand these were the first pictures we saw."},{"time":472704,"text":"The true comet rotation period\nis 12 and a half hours,"},{"time":475277,"text":"so this is accelerated,"},{"time":477366,"text":"but you will understand that\nour flight dynamics engineers thought,"},{"time":480617,"text":"this is not going to be\nan easy thing to land on."},{"time":484471,"text":"We had hoped for some kind\nof spud-like thing"},{"time":489115,"text":"where you could easily land."},{"time":491281,"text":"But we had one hope: maybe it was smooth."},{"time":494572,"text":"No. That didn't work either. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":498310,"text":"So at that point in time,\nit was clearly unavoidable:"},{"time":501003,"text":"we had to map this body\nin all the detail you could get,"},{"time":504534,"text":"because we had to find an area\nwhich is 500 meters in diameter and flat."},{"time":509687,"text":"Why 500 meters? That's the error\nwe have on landing the probe."},{"time":514286,"text":"So we went through this process,\nand we mapped the comet."},{"time":517467,"text":"We used a technique\ncalled photoclinometry."},{"time":519834,"text":"You use shadows thrown by the sun."},{"time":522064,"text":"What you see here is a rock\nsitting on the surface of the comet,"},{"time":525151,"text":"and the sun shines from above."},{"time":528077,"text":"From the shadow, we, with our brain,"},{"time":530236,"text":"can immediately determine\nroughly what the shape of that rock is."},{"time":533880,"text":"You can program that in a computer,"},{"time":535922,"text":"you then cover the whole comet,\nand you can map the comet."},{"time":540176,"text":"For that, we flew special trajectories\nstarting in August."},{"time":543856,"text":"First, a triangle\nof 100 kilometers on a side"},{"time":546765,"text":"at 100 kilometers' distance,"},{"time":548428,"text":"and we repeated the whole \nthing at 50 kilometers."},{"time":551432,"text":"At that time, we had seen the comet\nat all kinds of angles,"},{"time":555079,"text":"and we could use this technique\nto map the whole thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":559752,"text":"Now, this led to a selection\nof landing sites."},{"time":563019,"text":"This whole process we had to do,\nto go from the mapping of the comet"},{"time":567279,"text":"to actually finding\nthe final landing site, was 60 days."},{"time":570844,"text":"We didn't have more."},{"time":572230,"text":"To give you an idea,\nthe average Mars mission"},{"time":574350,"text":"takes hundreds of scientists\nfor years to meet"},{"time":578134,"text":"about where shall we go?"},{"time":580201,"text":"We had 60 days, and that was it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":582359,"text":"We finally selected the final landing site"},{"time":585402,"text":"and the commands were prepared\nfor Rosetta to launch Philae."},{"time":590455,"text":"The way this works is that Rosetta\nhas to be at the right point in space,"},{"time":594830,"text":"and aiming towards the comet,\nbecause the lander is passive."},{"time":597653,"text":"The lander is then pushed out\nand moves towards the comet."},{"time":601330,"text":"Rosetta had to turn around"},{"time":603120,"text":"to get its cameras to actually look\nat Philae while it was departing"},{"time":607677,"text":"and to be able to communicate with it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":610146,"text":"Now, the landing duration\nof the whole trajectory was seven hours."},{"time":614720,"text":"Now do a simple calculation:"},{"time":617507,"text":"if the velocity of Rosetta is off\nby one centimeter per second,"},{"time":621546,"text":"seven hours is 25,000 seconds."},{"time":625888,"text":"That means 252 meters wrong on the comet."},{"time":630253,"text":"So we had to know the velocity of Rosetta"},{"time":633597,"text":"much better than\none centimeter per second,"},{"time":636104,"text":"and its location in space\nbetter than 100 meters"},{"time":640168,"text":"at 500 million kilometers from Earth."},{"time":643372,"text":"That's no mean feat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":645740,"text":"Let me quickly take you through\nsome of the science and the instruments."},{"time":650129,"text":"I won't bore you with all the details\nof all the instruments,"},{"time":653565,"text":"but it's got everything."},{"time":655214,"text":"We can sniff gas,\nwe can measure dust particles,"},{"time":658348,"text":"the shape of them, the composition,"},{"time":660600,"text":"there are magnetometers, everything."},{"time":663108,"text":"This is one of the results from\nan instrument which measures gas density"},{"time":666707,"text":"at the position of Rosetta,"},{"time":668565,"text":"so it's gas which has left the comet."},{"time":670794,"text":"The bottom graph\nis September of last year."},{"time":673278,"text":"There is a long-term variation,\nwhich in itself is not surprising,"},{"time":676575,"text":"but you see the sharp peaks."},{"time":678456,"text":"This is a comet day."},{"time":680546,"text":"You can see the effect of the sun\non the evaporation of gas"},{"time":684656,"text":"and the fact that the comet is rotating."},{"time":687604,"text":"So there is one spot, apparently,"},{"time":689312,"text":"where there is a lot of stuff coming from,"},{"time":691459,"text":"it gets heated in the Sun,\nand then cools down on the back side."},{"time":694756,"text":"And we can see\nthe density variations of this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":698262,"text":"These are the gases\nand the organic compounds"},{"time":702395,"text":"that we already have measured."},{"time":704090,"text":"You will see it's an impressive list,"},{"time":705878,"text":"and there is much, much,\nmuch more to come,"},{"time":708362,"text":"because there are more measurements."},{"time":710308,"text":"Actually, there is a conference\ngoing on in Houston at the moment"},{"time":713656,"text":"where many of these results are presented."}]},{"cues":[{"time":716827,"text":"Also, we measured dust particles."},{"time":718448,"text":"Now, for you, this will not\nlook very impressive,"},{"time":721250,"text":"but the scientists were thrilled\nwhen they saw this."},{"time":724523,"text":"Two dust particles:"},{"time":725940,"text":"the right one they call Boris,\nand they shot it with tantalum"},{"time":728934,"text":"in order to be able to analyze it."},{"time":731048,"text":"Now, we found sodium and magnesium."},{"time":733439,"text":"What this tells you is this is\nthe concentration of these two materials"},{"time":737688,"text":"at the time the solar system was formed,"},{"time":740404,"text":"so we learned things about\nwhich materials were there"},{"time":743771,"text":"when the planet was made."}]},{"cues":[{"time":746859,"text":"Of course, one of the important\nelements is the imaging."},{"time":749577,"text":"This is one of the cameras of Rosetta,\nthe OSIRIS camera,"},{"time":752943,"text":"and this actually was the cover\nof Science magazine"},{"time":755938,"text":"on January 23 of this year."},{"time":758608,"text":"Nobody had expected\nthis body to look like this."},{"time":762046,"text":"Boulders, rocks -- if anything, it looks\nmore like the Half Dome in Yosemite"},{"time":765644,"text":"than anything else."},{"time":768151,"text":"We also saw things like this:"},{"time":770729,"text":"dunes, and what look to be,\non the righthand side, wind-blown shadows."},{"time":775651,"text":"Now we know these from Mars,\nbut this comet doesn't have an atmosphere,"},{"time":779575,"text":"so it's a bit difficult to create\na wind-blown shadow."},{"time":782454,"text":"It may be local outgassing,"},{"time":784439,"text":"stuff which goes up and comes back."},{"time":786622,"text":"We don't know, so there is\na lot to investigate."},{"time":789803,"text":"Here, you see the same image twice."},{"time":791893,"text":"On the left-hand side,\nyou see in the middle a pit."},{"time":794410,"text":"On the right-hand side,\nif you carefully look,"},{"time":796627,"text":"there are three jets coming out\nof the bottom of that pit."},{"time":799858,"text":"So this is the activity of the comet."},{"time":802155,"text":"Apparently, at the bottom of these pits\nis where the active regions are,"},{"time":806172,"text":"and where the material\nevaporates into space."},{"time":808935,"text":"There is a very intriguing crack\nin the neck of the comet."},{"time":812545,"text":"You see it on the right-hand side."},{"time":814541,"text":"It's a kilometer long,\nand it's two and a half meters wide."},{"time":818237,"text":"Some people suggest that actually,"},{"time":820483,"text":"when we get close to the sun,"},{"time":822551,"text":"the comet may split in two,"},{"time":824409,"text":"and then we'll have to choose,"},{"time":826089,"text":"which comet do we go for?"},{"time":828341,"text":"The lander -- again, lots of instruments,"},{"time":831514,"text":"mostly comparable except for the things\nwhich hammer in the ground and drill, etc."},{"time":836855,"text":"But much the same as Rosetta, and that is\nbecause you want to compare"},{"time":840732,"text":"what you find in space\nwith what you find on the comet."},{"time":844238,"text":"These are called\nground truth measurements."}]},{"cues":[{"time":846931,"text":"These are the landing descent images"},{"time":850162,"text":"that were taken by the OSIRIS camera."},{"time":852210,"text":"You see the lander getting further\nand further away from Rosetta."},{"time":856436,"text":"On the top right, you see an image\ntaken at 60 meters by the lander,"},{"time":860244,"text":"60 meters above the surface of the comet."},{"time":863100,"text":"The boulder there is some 10 meters."},{"time":865514,"text":"So this is one of the last images we took\nbefore we landed on the comet."},{"time":870228,"text":"Here, you see the whole sequence again,\nbut from a different perspective,"},{"time":873786,"text":"and you see three blown-ups\nfrom the bottom-left to the middle"},{"time":877971,"text":"of the lander traveling\nover the surface of the comet."},{"time":882156,"text":"Then, at the top, there is a before\nand an after image of the landing."},{"time":886342,"text":"The only problem with the after image is,\nthere is no lander."},{"time":890269,"text":"But if you carefully look\nat the right-hand side of this image,"},{"time":893540,"text":"we saw the lander still there, \nbut it had bounced."},{"time":897569,"text":"It had departed again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":899230,"text":"Now, on a bit of a comical note here"},{"time":902317,"text":"is that originally Rosetta was designed\nto have a lander which would bounce."},{"time":906937,"text":"That was discarded because\nit was way too expensive."},{"time":909510,"text":"Now, we forgot, but the lander knew."},{"time":911784,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":913388,"text":"During the first bounce,\nin the magnetometers,"},{"time":915895,"text":"you see here the data from them,\nfrom the three axes, x, y and z."},{"time":919725,"text":"Halfway through, you see a red line."},{"time":921931,"text":"At that red line, there is a change."},{"time":923765,"text":"What happened, apparently,\nis during the first bounce,"},{"time":927690,"text":"somewhere, we hit the edge of a crater\nwith one of the legs of the lander,"},{"time":932416,"text":"and the rotation velocity\nof the lander changed."},{"time":935236,"text":"So we've been rather lucky"},{"time":937209,"text":"that we are where we are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":939485,"text":"This is one of\nthe iconic images of Rosetta."},{"time":943154,"text":"It's a man-made object,\na leg of the lander,"},{"time":947077,"text":"standing on a comet."},{"time":949028,"text":"This, for me, is one of the very best\nimages of space science I have ever seen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":954159,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":959340,"text":"One of the things we still have to do\nis to actually find the lander."},{"time":963191,"text":"The blue area here\nis where we know it must be."},{"time":966887,"text":"We haven't been able to find it yet,\nbut the search is continuing,"},{"time":970505,"text":"as are our efforts to start getting\nthe lander to work again."},{"time":974270,"text":"We listen every day,"},{"time":976012,"text":"and we hope that between now\nand somewhere in April,"},{"time":978570,"text":"the lander will wake up again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":980308,"text":"The findings of what\nwe found on the comet:"},{"time":983795,"text":"This thing would float in water."},{"time":986251,"text":"It's half the density of water."},{"time":988875,"text":"So it looks like\na very big rock, but it's not."},{"time":991893,"text":"The activity increase we saw\nin June, July, August last year"},{"time":995539,"text":"was a four-fold activity increase."},{"time":997930,"text":"By the time we will be at the sun,"},{"time":999673,"text":"there will be 100 kilos\na second leaving this comet:"},{"time":1004246,"text":"gas, dust, whatever."},{"time":1005802,"text":"That's 100 million kilos a day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1009603,"text":"Then, finally, the landing day."},{"time":1011978,"text":"I will never forget -- absolute madness,\n250 TV crews in Germany."},{"time":1017366,"text":"The BBC was interviewing me,"},{"time":1019385,"text":"and another TV crew\nwho was following me all day"},{"time":1022357,"text":"were filming me being interviewed,"},{"time":1024493,"text":"and it went on like that\nfor the whole day."},{"time":1026931,"text":"The Discovery Channel crew"},{"time":1028742,"text":"actually caught me\nwhen leaving the control room,"},{"time":1031064,"text":"and they asked the right question,"},{"time":1033177,"text":"and man, I got into tears,\nand I still feel this."},{"time":1036802,"text":"For a month and a half,"},{"time":1038485,"text":"I couldn't think about\nlanding day without crying,"},{"time":1041319,"text":"and I still have the emotion in me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1044034,"text":"With this image of the comet,\nI would like to leave you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1046983,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1049096,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}